SUMMARY:Faith Community Network (in person)
DESCRIPTION:Can your faith community benefit by learning more about how to support your aging and seriously ill members?\nDo you want to learn how to expand the support you offer to your faith community? \nDuring each 1-hour session\, you will learn the most up-to-date information about these topics and how to put these principles into practice\nin your faith community. Our programs are practical and highly interactive. We will laugh\, cry\, and have fun! \nFor more information\, contact us at Community@transitionslifecare.org \nThese dates are part of a series happening throughout 2026. \nDifficult Conversations about Serious Illness Care\nWednesday\, April 22 \nTaking Your Congregational Care Team to the Next Level\nWednesday\, June 10 \nTips for Home-Based Caregiving\nWednesday\, July 22 \nCaregiver Self-Care\nWednesday\, September 9 \nThe Role of the Faith Community in Supporting People who are Seriously Ill\nWednesday\, October 14
URL:https://www.transitionslifecare.org/event/faith-community-network-in-person/2026-04-22/
LOCATION:Transitions LifeCare\, 250 Hospice Circle\, Raleigh\, NC\, 27607\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://www.transitionslifecare.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/hands-in-heart.png
ORGANIZER;CN="Community Engagement":MAILTO:community@transitionslifecare.org
GEO:35.8074456;-78.7418081
